## üîÑ Auto-Generation

**When Generated:**
- On every system boot
- Every hour (auto-sync)
- After manual sync

**How Generated:**
- Queen Bee Catalog Sync pulls updates from subordinate repositories
- AI analyzes and validates protocols (if enabled)
- Protocols organized by source node
- Both Markdown and JSON formats created

## üöÄ Usage

### View Human-Readable Catalogs

```bash
# View all protocols
cat catalogs/MASTER_CATALOG.md

# View Instrumentation protocols only
cat catalogs/node-instrumentation-shell-api-catalog.md

# View Syntheverse protocols only
cat catalogs/node-syntheverse-onramp-catalog.md
```

### Use JSON for Programmatic Access

```bash
# View as JSON
cat catalogs/master-catalog.json | jq '.'

# Count protocols per node
jq '.totalProtocols' catalogs/node-instrumentation-shell-api-catalog.json

# List protocol names
jq '.protocols[].protocol.name' catalogs/master-catalog.json
```

### In TypeScript/JavaScript

```typescript
import { readFileSync } from 'fs';

// Load catalog
const catalog = JSON.parse(
  readFileSync('catalogs/node-instrumentation-shell-api-catalog.json', 'utf-8')
);

// Access protocols
console.log('Node:', catalog.nodeName);
console.log('Total Protocols:', catalog.totalProtocols);

catalog.protocols.forEach(p => {
  console.log(`- ${p.protocol.name} v${p.protocol.version}`);
});
```

## üìä Catalog Structure

### Markdown Format

Organized for human readability:
- Node information header
- Protocol list with details
- Source repository links
- Version history

### JSON Format

Structured for programmatic access:
```json
{
  "nodeId": "node-id",
  "nodeName": "Node Name",
  "repository": "owner/repo",
  "lastSync": 1234567890,
  "totalProtocols": 10,
  "newProtocols": 2,
  "updatedProtocols": 1,
  "protocols": [...]
}
```

## üîç Finding Protocols

### By Source Node

**Need measurement protocols?**
‚Üí `node-instrumentation-shell-api-catalog.md`

**Need cloud/network protocols?**
‚Üí `node-syntheverse-onramp-catalog.md`

**Want overview of everything?**
‚Üí `MASTER_CATALOG.md`

### By Protocol Type

Use `grep` or `jq`:

```bash
# Find all API protocols
grep '"type": "api"' catalogs/*.json

# Find all protocols from specific node
jq '.protocols[] | select(.sourceNode == "node-instrumentation-shell-api")' catalogs/master-catalog.json
```
